	   <tr><td colspan=2>A question for those more experienced:<br>yesterday i was in a party camping the large orc camp in EC. Everything was going well, we were all progressing rapidly in exp... Until a Griffin Spawned Right above us. Ive seen some griffins around there but not at the camp. well, it either spawned or someone dragged it on us. <br>Anyhow, it proceeded to kill 2 of us so we all scattered. <br>As I was running away i made sure to check no one was following us and no one was so i climbed to the top of an overlooking hill and used my hide (successfully) and sat down to recover my hp and watch the griffin chew some ppl up. <br>I then noticed an orc leginairre (sp?) walking my way. I figured, Im hidden so ill just sit still. I conned him and he was indifferent to me so i just sat there and he walked right up to me an started whaling...<br>I guess my question is is why/how did he see me if i was hidden?? He was in the middle of being attacked by our group and was aggro'd but I wanst attacking him at all. and i sat for at least 30-40secs b4 he even came after me...<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Relsnaf<br>10 rogue Prexus</td></tr>
